======================================================================
PART 8: Connection to directed Hamiltonian cycles
======================================================================
  In a Ham cycle through 0:
    successor of 0 is always QR (0→succ ⟹ succ ∈ QR)
    predecessor of 0 is always NQR (pred→0 ⟹ -pred ∈ QR ⟹ pred ∈ NQR)

  In a Ham path from 0:
    first step goes to QR (0→v₁ ⟹ v₁ ∈ QR)
    last step: NQR bias decreases as p → ∞

  The NQR excess in path endpoints comes from the
  ASYMMETRIC first step: we start by entering QR territory,
  which means we're more likely to END in NQR territory
  (since we've 'used up' more QR vertices early on).

======================================================================
SUMMARY — The QR/NQR Decomposition
======================================================================

  H(P_p) = p × (p-1)/2 × (a + b)

  where a = paths from 0 to each QR vertex
        b = paths from 0 to each NQR vertex

  ╔═══╦═══════════╦══════════════╦═════════╦══════════╗
  ║ p ║     a     ║      b       ║   a+b   ║   b/a    ║
  ╠═══╬═══════════╬══════════════╬═════════╬══════════╣
  ║ 7 ║         1 ║            8 ║       9 ║ 8.000000 ║
  ║11 ║       628 ║        1,101 ║   1,729 ║ 1.753185 ║
  ║19 ║3040229428 ║ 3,817,640,437║         ║ 1.255807 ║
  ╚═══╩═══════════╩══════════════╩═════════╩══════════╝

  The b/a ratio → 1 as p → ∞ (QR/NQR become balanced)

  CHARACTER INTERPRETATION:
  h(0, v) = α + β × (v/p)  where α = (a+b)/2, β = (a-b)/2
  The DFT: ĥ(0, k) = -(a+b)/2 - (a-b)/2 × (k/p) × i√p

